Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.examples

package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.examples
This package contains several examples of how to use the bitstream tools contained in RapidSmith.
  • Related Packages
    Package
    Description
    edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.examples.support
    This package contains some supporting classes for the examples given in the bitstream tools in RapidSmith.
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    BitstreamDiff
    This executable loads two bitstreams and determines the differences.
    BitstreamManipulation
    Implements the same bitstream manipulation routines that Ben Sellers created in his original bitmanip tool.
    BitstreamSizeCalculator
     
    BitstreamSummary
    This executable prints the contents of a bitstream as an XML file.
    BRAMPartialBitstreams
    This example demonstrates how to create partial bitstreams for configuring the BRAMs on V4 devices.
    CheckFrameECC
     
    DebugBitstreamDecoder
    This example parses a debug bitstream and determines the size of each column.
    DeviceInformation
    Provides a main method that prints out information about a particular device.
    FrameAddressInfo
    Provides information about a frame address.
    FrameContents
    This method is used to print the contents of frames within the bitstream.
    FrameWriteSummary
    This example will search the bitstream for FDRI write commands and will summarize the FAR locations for each FDRI command.
    NonEmptyFrames
    This method is used to print the contents of non empty configured frames within the bitstream.
